Angola Says Oil Revenue Accounts For 71% of First-Quarter Budget Income

-- B y   C a n d i d o   M e n d e s
-- 
2011-05-24T10:43:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-24/angola-says-oil-revenue-accounts-for-71-of-first-quarter-budget-income.html
Angola ’s budget revenue was 939.6
billion kwanza ($10 billion) in the first quarter, of which 71
percent from from generated from oil, Finance Minister Carlos
Alberto Lopes said.  Oil revenue stood at 666 billion kwanza, Lopes told
lawmakers today in Luanda, the capital. Angola,  Africa ’s second-
biggest oil producer, pumped an average of 1.6 million barrels
of oil a day in the first quarter, less than a planned 1.9
million barrels, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Candido Mendes in Luanda at 
